div.b: Post Event Report Linux Day Milano 2024 2024-10-26

Attendance
We had a good attendance: while participants are not tracked as the event is open all day, we have an estimate (based o the occupancy of the rooms during talks) of about 200~250 people at any given time. Most of them didn't stay for the whole day, so we're probably looking around 350~400 unique visitors. We had a good mix of students and professionals from different IT fields, and we had some other local associations coming to staff booths and give talks.
Venue
The event was hosted by unixMiB in their university, which provided us with 4 classrooms with ~90 seats each. Compared to last year, all escalators worked perfectly and all vending machines were working. Everybody was able to get lunch either at the cafes in the area, or at the nearby Bicocca center. Positives :+1: GitHub swag was on time and SUPER appreciated Awesome speakers roaster Good participation
Negatives
We were not able to livestream the event this year Photos
Summary
Super nice event! The collaboration between university clubs was the only thing that made this possible, and it's awesome to see this event every year :)
